   Here is the 52-46 roll call by which the
Senate on Tuesday rejected an amendement calling for tougher auto
pollution controls than required by a compromise bill backed by
Senate leaders and the White House.
   On this vote, a ``yes'' vote was a vote to table, or reject, the
amendment, while a ``no'' vote was a vote not to table, that is, to
keep the amendment alive.
   Voting ``yes'' were 28 Democrats and 24 Republicans.
   Voting ``no'' were 27 Democrats and 19 Republicans.
   xxx denotes senators not voting.
